by Tobion at 2015-07-01T14:39:20Z

The PHP bug seems true: http://3v4l.org/Q1lpe

I guess it's because this timezone is not meant to be used anymore: http://php.net/manual/en/timezones.others.php
> Warning
Please do not use any of the timezones listed here (besides UTC), they only exist for backward compatible reasons.

But I think the change here makes sense anyway. When there is a timezone parameter we should use it instead of letting it being parsed from the string.

